title.narrative: Percentage of ER visits coming by ambulance (i) for selected diagnoses (MVA, cardiac, multiple symptoms); and (ii) where symptoms began in the last 12 hours

baseline.value: (i) 38% cardiac 45% MVA 45% multiple symptoms (ii) 62% of patientscoming to hospital by ambulance had symptoms starting 12 hoursorless

target.value: (i) 46% cardiac 56% MVA 52% multiple symptoms (ii) 80% starting<= 12 hours

comment.narrative: Multiple symptoms related-indicator and b) where symptoms began in the last 12 hours are dropped given that these indicators arenot well defined and not used.

title.narrative: Establishment of the enabling legislative environment for (i) EMS financing, (ii) separating of pre-hospital emergency services from PHC, (iii) establishing national management arrangements

comment.narrative: but on track. Clear progress on the institutional and policy front.

title.narrative: Proposals presented by MoH to make use of EU related funds

comment.narrative: Achieved. Croatia expected to access to EU in July 2013

title.narrative: Number of hospitals with integrated emergency reception area.
Percent of counties with EMS dispatch centers linked to 112 and TETRA

actual.value: 21 EMS linked to #112.1 to TETRAContract to pu

title.narrative: Field calls as percent of total calls (increase).

comment.narrative: Exceeded. All field calls are now related to the emergency system and no ambulances or emergency teams are being deployed formedical transportation or discharges. About 40 to 50% of these calls are classified as code red or orange which is a safe balancebetween red, orange and green calls

title.narrative: Response times from receipt of call to time at the scene

baseline.value: Average response time to scene is 16.8 minutes, with 28% of calls in less than or equal to 8 minutes, 20% less than or equal to 6minutes Average time from scene to hospital is 41.5 minutes

comment.narrative: This indicator was built using average times for “red” and “orange” priorities. It was agreed that the indicator should onlyinclude red priority cases. Given the lack of an operational definition of urban and rural areas, the system still reports theaverage time of all emergency calls. Nevertheless, the average is very close to the target for urban calls.

title.narrative: EMS teams per capita (decrease cross-county variation)

comment.narrative: Cross-county variation would be reduced to 0.3, but it will not achieve the target (0.2) because different population densitiesandgeographical distances cannot have similar number of teams per inhabitants in all regions

title.narrative: County variation in field calls per capita (decrease).

comment.narrative: All EMS units are reporting field calls

title.narrative: Croatian Institute of EMS has been established and is functioning.

actual.value: Legally Established in July 2009. Put into operation March 2010. Six of 29 staff members. 3 of 5 management committee members.Supporting the development of by-laws and rulebooks. Supporting the developmetn of County Institutes.

comment.narrative: Under development: Hospital Master plan, Outsourcing of non-medical hospital services; Public relations strategy; Applications forEU funds; Functional Review of the CIHI

title.narrative: Active involvement of MoH in EU funds utilization (measured through dedicated staff, Number of applications prepared by MoH, funds leveraged)

comment.narrative: Achieved. Project target in term of staff trained and draft applications developed (5 proposals); however, it should be noted thatthe number of applications approved is outside the Project’s influence. Additional training and support for PDO2 was financed withthe Project allowing the achieving of this PDO

title.narrative: Number of health professionals who have (i) begun training in EMS specialty according to national guidelines and (ii) received certification

comment.narrative: Component 2 - 26 people went to Romania (12), Austria (8), Estonia (6) Study Tours. 35 staff trained for developing proposals forEU funds. Component 1: 149 dispatchers
